The ENC-plot is an absolute statistic to evaluate the decisive factor in shaping codon usage bias. ENC values were taken into account for the background of the GC3s [63]. If codon usage is constrained only by G + C mutation bias, the expected ENC values would simply lie on or around the standard curve. Alternatively, other factors such as natural selection may play a major role in shaping codon usage bias. The ENC plots were calculated using the following formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
